<p>
Would you like to work with a great team of people at a rapidly growing tech company? Join <strong>4moms</strong>, a truly innovative consumer products company. We&#39;ve introduced robotics technology to the juvenile industry with our suite of high-tech baby gear, including the world&#39;s first power-folding stroller. We incorporate mechatronic technology and electronics into our products to expand their functions and increase ease-of-use. We design every product we make with intense attention to detail. We&rsquo;re always original, never a &ldquo;me-too&rdquo; company.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re one of America&rsquo;s fastest-growing companies and the best is yet to come! 4moms was honored with the 2011 Kind &amp; Jugend Innovation Award, listed as one of the Top Ten Best Places to Work in Western PA in 2011, and our products have also won the JPMA Innovation Award, the iParenting Media Award, and the National Parenting Center Seal of Approval.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>About You</strong></p>
<p>
The best candidates for these&nbsp;<strong>Robotics/Mechanical Engineer</strong>&nbsp;positions will be energetic, take initiative and have a broad understanding of mechanical engineering, as well as reasonable understanding in electrical and/or software engineering. The ability to work independently is a must as well as being able to fit in with a very dynamic and close knit team.</p>
<p>
<strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<p>
The ideal candidate will possess most of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>
B.S. in Mechanical Engineering</li>
<li>
M.S. in Mechanical Engineering, Mechatronics, Robotics, or similar preferred</li>
<li>
Experience in product development lifecycle preferred</li>
<li>
Product team leadership experience a plus</li>
<li>
Proficiency in 3D CAD (Solidworks preferred)</li>
<li>
Experience in FEM analysis is a plus</li>
<li>
Proficiency in MS Office Products (Word, Excel, Powerpoint)</li>
<li>
Willingness to learn and Can-Do Attitude</li>
</ul>
<p>
In return for your services, we currently offer a generous total compensation plan including a competitive salary, company paid medical, dental, life &amp; disability insurance, a 401(k) plan with company match, and an iPhone.</p>
