<p>
Would you like to work with a great team of people at a rapidly growing tech company? Join 4moms, a truly innovative consumer products company. We&#39;ve introduced robotics technology to the juvenile industry with our suite of high-tech baby gear, including the world&#39;s first power-folding stroller. We incorporate mechatronic technology and electronics into our products to expand their functions and increase ease-of-use. We design every product we make with intense attention to detail. We&rsquo;re always original, never a &ldquo;me-too&rdquo; company.</p>
<p>
<strong>About You:</strong></p>
<p>
The best candidates for the <strong>Reliability/Test Engineer</strong> position will be energetic, take initiative and have a broad understanding of mechanical engineering, as well as reasonable understanding in electrical and/or software engineering. The ability to work independently is a must as well as being able to fit in with a very dynamic and close knit team.</p>
<p>
<strong>What you&rsquo;ll be doing:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develop reliability test plans for complex, highly engineered electro-mechanical products and implement the tests.</li>
<li>
Work with engineering to embed reliability requirements in product specifications.</li>
<li>
Design and build appropriate test fixtures, control systems and setups.</li>
<li>
Review designs through leading the internal FMEA processes.</li>
<li>
Lead design validation efforts on products in conjunction with Engineering, Compliance and Quality.</li>
<li>
Work with design teams to analyze and resolve any issues arising from durability&nbsp;testing.</li>
<li>
Perform statistical analysis of product reliability from reliability test results.</li>
<li>
Manage multiple reliability projects simultaneously.</li>
<li>
Mentor engineering staff in Reliability concepts as needed.</li>
</ul>
<br />
<p>
<strong>Must Haves:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
BS in Mechanial Engineering, Reliability Engineering or equivalent,&nbsp;&nbsp;MS preferred</li>
<li>
5+ years Reliability Engineering experience with electromechanical products including experience in Reliability tools and analysis</li>
<li>
Proven experience in developing test specifications and designing test fixtures.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Excellent written, oral, and presentation skills.&nbsp; Must be able to effectively communicate with co-workers, suppliers and management.</li>
<li>
Experience with SolidWorks and knowledge of software reliability preferred</li>
</ul>
<p>
We&rsquo;re one of America&rsquo;s fastest-growing companies and the best is yet to come! 4moms was honored with the 2011 Kind &amp; Jugend Innovation Award, listed as one of the Top Ten Best Places to Work in Western PA in 2011, and our products have also won the JPMA Innovation Award, the iParenting Media Award, and the National Parenting Center Seal of Approval.</p>
<p>
In return for your services, we currently offer a generous total compensation plan including a competitive salary, company paid medical, dental, life &amp; disability insurance, a 401(k) plan with company match, and an iPhone.</p>
