			<description><![CDATA[<p>
4moms <strong>Senior Plastics Design/Process Engineers</strong> are energetic, take initiative, and have an extensive understanding of engineered plastics part design, mold tooling design, fabrication &amp; cost, plastic materials properties, and plastic materials processing.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
Within the scope of responsibilities, they provide clear, comprehensive, hands on technical guidance and leadership to 4moms Product Development Teams, Supply Chain Engineering, and our manufacturing partners.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>What you&rsquo;ll be doing:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Provides expert guidance in engineering plastic materials selection, and design for molding for New Product Development (NPD) Projects.</li>
<li>
Participates and contributes to Design Reviews for NPD Projects and changes to existing products.</li>
<li>
Reviews, approves tooling plans/proposals with respect to cost, cavitation, materials of construction, complexity, processing time, expected life, maintenance planning, and warranty requirements.</li>
<li>
Working with Finance &amp; Accounting team, develops appropriate amortization plans for new tooling and develops tooling replacement and tooling contingency planning budgets.</li>
<li>
Audits existing and potential OEM Partners molding and tooling operations and where applicable, develops mitigation/improvement plans and timelines.</li>
<li>
Understands optimization techniques including DoE and Scientific Molding.</li>
<li>
Identifies and implements cost improvement/containment, and performance improvement strategies for existing molded parts.&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Evaluates and approves alternative engineering plastic materials.</li>
<li>
Where possible, seeks opportunities for economy of scale in the selection of plastic materials.</li>
<li>
Stays current on tool design and advances in molding techniques.</li>
<li>
Applying technical skills and experience, provides expert plastic part failure analysis and resolution paths.</li>
<li>
Oversees Mold Flow analyses, reviews results for accuracy and relevancy, and makes recommendations for improving part/tool design.</li>
<li>
Assists in the development of quality assurance testing requirements for engineering plastic components.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<br />
<strong>What we need from you:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Develops trust and strong working relationships with internal customers and OEM Partners, both domestic and offshore.</li>
<li>
Consistent with 4moms culture, takes the leadership role in developing/sharing plastic part design/processing best practices.</li>
<li>
Experience working with offshore contract manufacturers strongly desired.</li>
<li>
Demonstrated strong technical writing and communication skills</li>
<li>
Previous experience with critical to safety plastic products would be a plus</li>
<li>
Ability to speak/write Mandarin or Cantonese would be a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
B.S. in Mechanical, Manufacturing, or Materials Science Engineering</li>
<li>
M.S. in Mechanical or Manufacturing Engineering, or recognized Plastics Materials Program, preferred</li>
<li>
Minimum of 10 years experience in roles of progressively increasing responsibilities in plastic mold tooling design and optimization, plastic part design, material selection, material processing, and molding process controls.</li>
<li>
Proficiency in MS Office Products (Word, Excel, Powerpoint)</li>
<li>
Proficiency in use of popular CAD/CAM and Design Analysis software.</li>
<li>
Willingness to learn and Can-Do Attitude</li>
<li>
Ability to travel domestically and internationally</li>
</ul>
<p>
We&rsquo;re one of America&rsquo;s fastest-growing companies and the best is yet to come! 4moms was honored with the 2011 Kind &amp; Jugend Innovation Award, listed as one of the Top Ten Best Places to Work in Western PA in 2011, and our products have also won the JPMA Innovation Award, the iParenting Media Award, and the National Parenting Center Seal of Approval.</p>
<p>
In return for your services, we currently offer a generous total compensation plan including a competitive salary, company paid medical, dental, life &amp; disability insurance, a 401(k) plan with company match, and an iPhone.</p>
